  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Up to this day, I don't know if this was a false piece of paper or they obtained it by this German commander, and he did it on his-- on his own, or he-- or he was bribed, or something.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But anyway, it gave us, already-- we had a German paper and we had a Ukrainian paper.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It gave us a little bit confidence that we are going to try to get back to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "At the same time, we asked them if they-- you know, between Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur is 10 days.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] They said that they will be able to-- to provide for us, for money, a guy.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because we want to go from Horodenka to the city of Stanislau, which was a long, a long distance, in a large city-- over 100,000 population.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In Poland, you know, those were the large, large-- because they were large cities-- not like in America-- millions.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anyway, and from there, we wanted to go back to the area which is close to Torun, because we figured if we will be-- we know the area in Torun on the-- on the other side.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So given we went out-- when we went out from the Judenrat there, from the office, we saw a soldier out standing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The soldiers-- the Hungarian soldiers-- were coming out to sell stuff.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Some of the soldiers were being rotated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I told you that Horodenka was a hub where the Hungarian new soldiers-- you know-- the-- the-- the military front was 100-- hundreds of miles deeper inside Russia at that time yet.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this soldier-- they-- they-- they-- they felt lost no matter how big anti-Semites they were.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they only spoke a Hungarian language that has no-- no similar language in Europe.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
